# React Event Handling Mastery Checklist

## Beginner → Veteran (First-Principles Roadmap)

> Core First Principle:
>
> React applications become useful only when users can interact with them.
>
> **User Action → Event → Event Handler → State Change → Re-render → UI Update**
>
> Everything in React Event Handling exists to manage this flow.

---

# Phase 0: Foundation

## Understand Why Events Exist

* [ ] Explain what an event is
* [ ] Explain why applications need events
* [ ] Explain the relationship between user actions and UI updates
* [ ] Understand React's event-driven architecture
* [ ] Understand the flow:

```text
User Action
↓
Event Fired
↓
Handler Executes
↓
State Changes
↓
Component Re-renders
↓
UI Updates
```

### Milestone

* [ ] Explain event handling without using React terminology

