# Phase 2: Event Handling Basics

## Learn React Event Syntax

### Basic Event Handler

* [ ] Attach click handlers

```jsx
<button onClick={handleClick}>
  Click
</button>
```

### Understand Difference from HTML

* [ ] Compare HTML events vs React events

HTML

```html
<button onclick="doSomething()">
```

React

```jsx
<button onClick={doSomething}>
```

### Milestone

* [ ] Create buttons that trigger functions correctly

---

# Phase 3: Event Handler Functions

## Learn Handler Creation

### Named Functions

* [ ] Create reusable handlers

```jsx
function handleClick() {}
```

### Arrow Functions

* [ ] Use arrow handlers

```jsx
const handleClick = () => {};
```

### Inline Handlers

* [ ] Use inline handlers safely

```jsx
<button onClick={() => alert("Clicked")}>
```

### Milestone

* [ ] Know when to use named vs inline handlers

---

# Phase 4: Passing Data to Event Handlers

## Learn Argument Passing

### Basic Parameters

* [ ] Pass values to handlers

```jsx
<button onClick={() => deleteUser(id)}>
```

### Multiple Parameters

* [ ] Pass multiple values

```jsx
<button onClick={() => updateUser(id, role)}>
```

### Understand Execution Timing

* [ ] Explain why this is wrong:

```jsx
<button onClick={deleteUser(id)}>
```

* [ ] Explain why this is correct:

```jsx
<button onClick={() => deleteUser(id)}>
```

### Milestone

* [ ] Pass dynamic values without triggering premature execution

